COMBINATORS IN CSS

Descedant- it matches all descendant elements that are inside ancestor, no matter how deeply nested.

The child selector targets only the direct children of an element not grandchildren or deeper descendants.

The adjacent sibling selector selects an element that is immediately next to another element — they must be siblings in the HTML and directly follow one another.